		    News file for MMUX Bash Pointers
		    ================================


Revision 0.1.0-devel.1
----------------------

* Updated to require GNU Automake at least version 1.17 and GNU Autoconf
  at least version 2.72.

* Added "unalias" usages to remove aliases when unloading the library.

* Added array accessors and mutators.

* Added support for C language type "uintmax_t".

* Renamed nickname of "intmax_t" from "intmax" to "sintmax".

* Renamed nickname of "intptr_t" from "intptr" to "sintptr".

* The following  standard types are handled  through their corresponding,
  equivalent,  signed  or  unsigned,   integer  type:  ssize_t,  size_t,
  intmax_t,  uintmax_t, intptr_t,  uintptr_t,  off_t, pid_t,  ptrdiff_t,
  mode_t, uid_t, gid_t.

* Added predicate builtins to validate  the string representation of the
  supported C language types.


Revision 0.1.0-devel.0
----------------------

* Initial development release.


